oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Mrs. Ed McNish with 200 lb. wild boar she killed in Cherokee National Forest, Tenn.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of Mrs. Ed McNish of Nashville, Tennsesee and the 200 lb. wild boar she killed in the Cherokee National Forest. She is pictured at a campsite with two tents in the background. She is wearing a coat and long pants and holding a bow in her right hand with arrows in a holster on the left side of her body. The boar is tied to a branch.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
